# Changelog Maintenance

When completing work that constitutes a **notable change**, add an entry to `CHANGELOG.md` under `## [Unreleased]` before finishing.

## What counts as notable

| Notable (update changelog) | Not notable (skip) |
|---|---|
| New feature or endpoint | Typo fixes, comment edits |
| Bug fix affecting behavior | Internal refactors with no behavior change |
| Breaking or deprecated API | Dev tooling / CI-only changes |
| Dependency upgrade with impact | Test-only changes |
| Security fix | Lint / formatting cleanup |
| Schema or migration change | Documentation-only updates |

## Format

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) categories:

- **Added** — new features or capabilities
- **Changed** — changes to existing functionality
- **Deprecated** — soon-to-be-removed features
- **Removed** — removed features
- **Fixed** — bug fixes
- **Security** — vulnerability patches

Each entry: `- **Scope**: Brief description of what changed and why`

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Added

- **Profiles**: Endpoint for bulk profile import via CSV
```

## Rules

1. Always place entries under `## [Unreleased]` — never invent a version number.
2. Create only the category subsections that have entries (don't add empty `- N/A` sections).
3. Keep entries concise — one line per change, grouped by scope.
4. When a release is cut, the user moves `[Unreleased]` items into a versioned section.
